                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1169-1">AMS, II, 631- 34 ; BHO, 126.
Suhadii', II, 380-84.
References dans DTC, XII, col. 175- 76 (E.Tisserant) , s.v. Babovai, et dans DHGE,
VI, col. 31 (E. Herman), s.v. Babovai.
S. Gero, Barsauma of Nisibis and Persian Christianity in the Fifth Century
(Louvain, 1981 ; CSCO 426, Subsidia 63) , 97-109.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1169">In hagiography: Mar Bawai was commemorated
          as the Catholicos of the Church of the East from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/1889">Tella</placeName>. He was born a Zoroastrian and
          converted to Christianity through his encounter with a monk called Mar Abda from Qunni. He
          became a monk and was elected patriarch. His tenure was marked by the efforts of his
            rival <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/369">Barsauma</persName> to "Nestorianize"
          the Church of the East. Bawai was killed, perhaps because Barsauma had accused him of
          being an enemy of the Sasanian empire.</note>
